==English==

===Etymology===
Russian '''[[царь]]''' ''(tsar’),'' from Old Russian '''[[цьсарь]]''' ''(tsĭsarĭ),'' from Old Church Slavonic '''[[цѣсарь]]''' ''(tsěsarĭ),'' from Latin '''[[caesar]]'''.

===Noun===
'''czar'''
# An [[emperor]] of [[Russia]].

